episodes.title: DJ KITTY GLITTER MIXSET #114 - TRASHPALACE
episodes.description:
The year was 2007. Sydney nightlife was peaking. I had only just started Dj’ing and was already playing in most of the venues on Oxford St 4 nights a week. I decided to do an after-hours event called TRASHPALACE. It was on the first floor of The Oxford from 4am until 10am every Sunday morning. It proved an instant success and just a few weeks later we started doing it both Saturday and Sunday mornings. Week after week, hundreds of insatiable party people from all over Sydney packed in from wherever they were clubbing to keep on truckin’ on.
It was such a mixed crowd of off-chops all sorts that all sorts of mayhem and magic happened. 
OH the sights I saw on that dancefloor!
This mixset is a flashback to that time and energy of 2007 & ’08.
I will be forever grateful for the love I felt from everyone during those early years. Your encouragement propelled me to DJ’ing worldwide!
The pandemic has been tough for so many. A year without disco lights and dancing is a nightmare for me, but I am blessed to be home with family. 
I hope we can all get fabulous & trashy again soon. I can’t wait to get the green light to party!!! 
Until then, keep smiling, keep shining & stay safe.

Your contributions go towards my monthly subscription fees. Thank you for listening, Love Kitty xox
PAYPAL - www.paypal.me/djkittyglitter VENMO - www.venmo.com/DJKittyGlitter

episodes.title: DJ KITTY GLITTER MIXSET #93 CLUB LOVE COCKTAIL PARTY
episodes.description:
In November 2017 I was thrilled to be invited to play at Elton John AIDS Foundations CLUB LOVE fundraising event in London. The night raised over one million pounds to support people living with HIV. 

I was directed to play a cocktail/disco/glitter set for the start of the evening as 100's of Londons highest society guests arrived for cocktails and good vibes before being ushered into the main room for the dinner and show. I then closed the night out as the last Dj at the after-party. 

Here's some vibes that set the tone for what was a sensational affaire with big THANKS to Elton John & David Furnish for their outstanding humanitarian efforts.

Releasing this mixset on the day that my home Australia joined many other countries around the world by legalising same sex marriage only resonates a CLUB LOVE message - United we can make the world a better place for everyone . LOVE IS LOVE
